1. Install node. I am currently using 0.10.24.

2. Install express globally for ease of use.

$ npm install -g express

3. Create the base nodesite application.

$ express -e nodesite
$ cd nodesite
$ npm install

4. Check that we have the template application installed.

$ node app

Point the browser at localhost:3000 and see if the page exists.

5. Start a git repository for the project.

$ git init

6. Create a .gitignore file and add a line to omit the modules that are installed in the local module directory.

# Omit local modules.
node_modules/

$ git add .

7. Add the mongodb and mongoose support to node.
$ npm install mongodb
$ npm install mongoose

8. Install mocha for testing.
$ sudo npm install -g mocha

9. Install gulp for building.
$ sudo npm install -g gulp

10. Install gulp for local project builds
$ npm install gulp
